<item>
            <title>[LU-5293] Removing index files on quota slaves</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5293</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The new quota infrastructure was designed to support the removal of the index files on slaves. We actually needed to do that for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5247&quot; title=&quot;Strange quota limits on OSTs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5247&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5247&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. While it seems to work fine with master, we are not able to remount the OST with lustre 2.4.&lt;br/&gt;
We really need to add a new sanity-quota tests exercising this. Actually, having a mount option to destroy quota slave indexes would be very useful as well.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
